gomodel:SYNGO_3867  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: Fig.1: \"Interaction and co-localization of CPEB-containing cytoplasmic complex proteins\"\n- \"To assess whether these components were co-localized in dendrites, cultured neurons were coimmunostained for symplekin and each other factor and 3D deconvolved images were analyzed (Figure 1G). CPEB, PARN, Gld2 and Ngd were non-randomly co-localized with symplekin (p > 0.95), while GluR1 was not (Figure 1H). \"\n- \"These proteins were also detected in dendritic spines; 3D reconstructions of phalloidin fluorescence (Figure 1J) showed that 23.1% ± 1.24% of spines contained symplekin and 80.1% ± 2.54% of symplekin-positive spines also contained CPEB, Gld2, PARN, or Ngd immunoreactivity (n=40 cells, 1196 spines). These data indicate that the cytoplasmic polyadenylation machinery forms complexes in dendrites and at synapses.\". Experimental description: - \"Rat hippocampal neuron cultures were prepared as described\"" ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2514-0216" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2286-1587" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0003-0593-3443" ;
        dc:date           "2018-07-09" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_CC_3867" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10116" .

